1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:09,107
=Episode 18=

14
00:01:27,779 --> 00:01:29,418
If you need space,

15
00:01:29,419 --> 00:01:30,418
I'll give you space.

16
00:01:30,419 --> 00:01:31,778
If you need time

17
00:01:31,779 --> 00:01:33,258
to sort out what you want to say,

18
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:34,739
I'll be patient.

19
00:01:35,219 --> 00:01:36,819
If things get dangerous

20
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:38,618
or too much to handle alone,

21
00:01:38,619 --> 00:01:40,060
call me.

22
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:42,659
I promise.

23
00:01:45,259 --> 00:01:47,620
It's a little gift to mark
our first month together.

24
00:01:47,940 --> 00:01:49,618
There are two names on it.

25
00:01:49,619 --> 00:01:50,858
One is Florence Nightingale,

26
00:01:50,859 --> 00:01:52,724
and the other is you.

27
00:01:52,725 --> 00:01:55,657
♪Just say yes♪

28
00:01:56,050 --> 00:01:58,495
♪And I won't go♪

29
00:01:59,062 --> 00:02:02,370
♪Don't leave me standing♪

30
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,698
♪All alone♪

31
00:02:04,699 --> 00:02:06,019
We're really

32
00:02:06,020 --> 00:02:07,539
together now.

33
00:02:07,540 --> 00:02:08,618
From now on,

34
00:02:08,619 --> 00:02:10,218
I want you to tell me everything.

35
00:02:10,219 --> 00:02:11,899
Anything at all.

36
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,818
Just tell me.

37
00:02:13,819 --> 00:02:15,139
I'll do everything I can

38
00:02:15,140 --> 00:02:16,538
to help you through it.

39
00:02:16,539 --> 00:02:17,859
That's what

40
00:02:17,860 --> 00:02:19,461
a husband is supposed to do.

41
00:02:19,462 --> 00:02:21,282
♪Just say yes♪

42
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,570
♪And I won't go♪

43
00:02:25,575 --> 00:02:28,157
♪Don't leave me standing♪

44
00:02:29,619 --> 00:02:30,899
Xu Nange,

45
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,419
don't run this time.

46
00:02:32,587 --> 00:02:35,861
♪The warmth we shared,
the time we spent♪

47
00:02:35,862 --> 00:02:41,107
♪Don't think you cry in love again♪

48
00:02:42,187 --> 00:02:47,620
♪Say yes♪

49
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:49,058
(Work Module Setup)
The materials from

50
00:02:49,059 --> 00:02:50,440
the tech team are now very clear.

51
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,058
Regarding the break-in
at Mrs. Huo's lab,

52
00:02:52,059 --> 00:02:53,338
nothing was damaged,

53
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:54,618
nor taken,

54
00:02:54,619 --> 00:02:55,539
but

55
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:58,099
files were copied.

56
00:03:00,137 --> 00:03:02,857
(Cooperative Institution Plan)

57
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:04,900
You just mentioned

58
00:03:05,379 --> 00:03:07,459
Dr. X's latest paper

59
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:09,099
is targeting United Pharma?

60
00:03:09,339 --> 00:03:10,259
That's right.

61
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:16,939
Do you understand
what the worst case looks like?

62
00:03:18,580 --> 00:03:20,139
If anyone finds out

63
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:21,900
that Nange is Dr. X,

64
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,300
and that she's

65
00:03:23,379 --> 00:03:25,620
out to bring down United Pharma,

66
00:03:25,659 --> 00:03:27,620
her life will be in danger.

67
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:28,699
Sir...

68
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:29,618
Just go home.

69
00:03:29,619 --> 00:03:30,419
Keep an eye on her

70
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:32,060
and make sure she's safe.

71
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:33,580
But what about you?

72
00:03:45,379 --> 00:03:47,859
You've been busy all day, haven't you?

73
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:50,460
I feel like I haven't seen you all day.

74
00:03:50,580 --> 00:03:53,220
You know, it's always
been you giving me gifts.

75
00:03:53,339 --> 00:03:54,778
So today I got you

76
00:03:54,779 --> 00:03:56,060
a little gift too.

77
00:03:56,339 --> 00:03:57,459
Fair warning though.

78
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:58,899
It wasn't expensive.

79
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,659
It's just from the heart.

80
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:02,460
I hope you'll like it.

81
00:04:04,539 --> 00:04:05,538
Mrs. Huo

82
00:04:05,539 --> 00:04:06,620
is not at home?

83
00:04:09,860 --> 00:04:10,498
Hello?

84
00:04:10,499 --> 00:04:11,538
Where are you?

85
00:04:11,539 --> 00:04:13,300
I've finally reached you.

86
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:15,739
Tell me where you are.

87
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,460
I'm out shopping.

88
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:30,338
(Hello, the number you have dialed)

89
00:04:30,339 --> 00:04:32,179
(is currently unavailable.)

90
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:38,858
Shen Yan, hurry up.

91
00:04:38,859 --> 00:04:39,979
On it.

92
00:04:46,099 --> 00:04:48,379
(Hello, the number you have dialed)

93
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:50,220
(is currently unavailable.)

94
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:52,820
Can you go any faster?

95
00:04:53,099 --> 00:04:54,220
Got it.

96
00:05:05,850 --> 00:05:11,974
♪All of my dreams, leading me here♪

97
00:05:11,975 --> 00:05:18,157
♪Fueling the fire
that help me fight all the fear♪

98
00:05:18,325 --> 00:05:24,232
♪All that I've got, and all that I am♪

99
00:05:24,537 --> 00:05:30,470
♪All that I gave up
just to stand where I stand♪

100
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:37,157
♪Every step that I took was toward you♪

101
00:05:39,859 --> 00:05:40,900
Huo Beiyan!

102
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:47,070
♪I found what I've been looking for♪

103
00:05:47,325 --> 00:05:53,232
♪Don't have to keep searching anymore♪

104
00:05:53,412 --> 00:05:59,695
♪I've never thought I'd have it all♪

105
00:05:59,862 --> 00:06:06,036
♪But everything changed,
and anything is possible♪

106
00:06:06,037 --> 00:06:12,120
♪I found what I've been looking for♪

107
00:06:21,987 --> 00:06:27,770
♪I found what I've been looking for♪

108
00:06:28,225 --> 00:06:33,945
♪Don't have to keep searching anymore♪

109
00:06:34,537 --> 00:06:40,232
♪I never thought I'd have it all♪

110
00:06:40,462 --> 00:06:46,586
♪But everything changed,
and anything is possible♪

111
00:06:46,587 --> 00:06:56,382
♪I found what I've been looking for♪

112
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,059
What happened?

113
00:07:08,659 --> 00:07:10,340
Why wasn't your phone going through?

114
00:07:11,419 --> 00:07:13,379
I was going to go out this afternoon

115
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:14,978
to get you a gift.

116
00:07:14,979 --> 00:07:17,178
And somehow I managed
to drop my phone in the water.

117
00:07:17,179 --> 00:07:19,020
- After that...
- Xu Nange,

118
00:07:19,779 --> 00:07:21,140
I have a question for you.

119
00:07:21,779 --> 00:07:23,380
The two-week countdown is up.

120
00:07:24,219 --> 00:07:26,099
You owe me a straight answer.

121
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:28,940
Come with me.

122
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:38,978
The order to the front desk

123
00:07:38,979 --> 00:07:40,059
came from me.

124
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,299
No visitors, including you.

125
00:07:43,620 --> 00:07:44,659
Why?

126
00:07:45,739 --> 00:07:47,819
The day before, I received
an anonymous letter.

127
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:49,619
At the same time, I confirmed something.

128
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,859
It turned out

129
00:07:52,779 --> 00:07:55,978
that the Dr. X I'd been searching for

130
00:07:55,979 --> 00:07:57,419
had been right beside me.

131
00:08:00,299 --> 00:08:02,459
I was going to bring it up in two weeks.

132
00:08:02,460 --> 00:08:03,178
NIT-33,

133
00:08:03,179 --> 00:08:04,940
did you develop it?

134
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,619
What?

135
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:12,459
Answer me.

136
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:13,700
Did you,

137
00:08:13,979 --> 00:08:15,260
or didn't you?

138
00:08:15,299 --> 00:08:16,780
Of course not.

139
00:08:17,979 --> 00:08:19,538
Then three years ago,

140
00:08:19,539 --> 00:08:21,739
that paper on NIT-33,

141
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:23,140
didn't you write it?

142
00:08:24,779 --> 00:08:26,098
Access to NIT's

143
00:08:26,099 --> 00:08:27,579
original molecular structure data

144
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:29,659
was limited to United
Pharma insiders only.

145
00:08:29,779 --> 00:08:31,580
Master's internship at Linhai.

146
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:34,139
United Pharma New
Product Evaluation Division.

147
00:08:34,579 --> 00:08:35,820
Six months.

148
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:37,099
What are you saying?

149
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:38,139
Yes.

150
00:08:38,579 --> 00:08:40,818
I did intern at United Pharma.

151
00:08:40,819 --> 00:08:43,499
I didn't just know NIT-33 was dangerous.

152
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,778
I tried everything

153
00:08:44,779 --> 00:08:46,619
to gather evidence.

154
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:48,099
I wanted the public to know.

155
00:08:48,459 --> 00:08:49,298
But United Pharma

156
00:08:49,299 --> 00:08:50,739
used every trick in the book

157
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:52,298
to bury all the damaging data,

158
00:08:52,299 --> 00:08:54,000
and pushed the clinical
trials through faster.

159
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:55,298
Until today,

160
00:08:55,299 --> 00:08:57,899
I still haven't found
solid evidence to prove it.

161
00:08:58,459 --> 00:08:59,739
That's why

162
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:02,739
NIT-33 is still selling
overseas to this day.

163
00:09:02,939 --> 00:09:05,139
I've known about its
harm for a long time.

164
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:06,139
But,

165
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:08,220
I've done everything I possibly could.

166
00:09:08,539 --> 00:09:09,619
I'm not powerful enough.

167
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:11,540
I can't bring it down that fast.

168
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,619
It wasn't until two days ago

169
00:09:17,939 --> 00:09:20,300
that I found out
exactly who it had hurt.

170
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:24,139
Beiyan, did you know?

171
00:09:24,459 --> 00:09:26,660
Grandma is the person

172
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:28,540
who's been supporting
me all these years.

173
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:31,418
On the transfer slips,

174
00:09:31,419 --> 00:09:33,099
no real name was ever written.

175
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,298
Just a single

176
00:09:34,299 --> 00:09:36,698
letter of the alphabet.

177
00:09:36,699 --> 00:09:37,700
X.

178
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:49,340
So you believed

179
00:09:49,659 --> 00:09:52,300
Dr. X was an accomplice
of United Pharma,

180
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:54,899
and finding her was
about getting revenge.

181
00:09:59,779 --> 00:10:00,700
Yes.

182
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:04,139
I wanted justice for Grandma.

183
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,499
Under the name Dr. X,

184
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,979
over the past three years,
I've published seven papers.

185
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:12,619
They're all point to the risks

186
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:14,058
of NIT-33 and similar drugs.

187
00:10:14,059 --> 00:10:16,300
I really want to bring
this into the open.

188
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:23,940
I'm sorry.

189
00:10:24,860 --> 00:10:25,739
I misjudged you.

190
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,540
I should have told you sooner.

191
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:28,899
Because I knew

192
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,019
this isn't just an academic dispute.

193
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:32,058
United Pharma has

194
00:10:32,059 --> 00:10:33,859
very powerful reach overseas.

195
00:10:34,699 --> 00:10:35,418
My papers

196
00:10:35,419 --> 00:10:37,580
strike at their core product.

197
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:38,979
It cuts off their revenue

198
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:40,418
and destroys their foundation.

199
00:10:40,419 --> 00:10:41,259
Every person who knows

200
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:41,938
who I am

201
00:10:41,939 --> 00:10:43,580
is another risk.

202
00:10:44,539 --> 00:10:46,540
Beiyan, I didn't want to
drag you into this.

203
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:51,298
And I only found out today

204
00:10:51,299 --> 00:10:53,779
that you'd become a
shareholder of United Pharma.

205
00:11:01,539 --> 00:11:03,540
I became a shareholder of United Pharma.

206
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:06,019
Not to invest,

207
00:11:06,659 --> 00:11:07,820
but to infiltrate.

208
00:11:08,579 --> 00:11:10,379
I need to find from the inside

209
00:11:10,699 --> 00:11:12,058
every piece of paper

210
00:11:12,059 --> 00:11:13,940
that could put them in prison.

211
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:16,979
But once my next batch
of evidence goes public,

212
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:18,499
United Pharma will take a major hit,

213
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,379
and Huo Group will get
caught in the fallout.

214
00:11:20,539 --> 00:11:21,899
Ye Xin is not a good person.

215
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,739
She will try to take you down with her.

216
00:11:27,059 --> 00:11:28,180
That's fine.

217
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,220
Grandma's life's work

218
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,580
wasn't Huo Group's market value.

219
00:11:32,659 --> 00:11:33,739
It was

220
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:37,060
the belief that medicine
exists to save lives.

221
00:11:37,939 --> 00:11:39,298
When Grandma was still herself,

222
00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:40,859
she set one rule for the family.

223
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:41,940
Huo Group

224
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:43,979
doesn't need to be the biggest company,

225
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,619
But it must be the cleanest.

226
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:48,379
We earn only honest money.

227
00:11:49,699 --> 00:11:51,779
That's the foundation of who we are.

228
00:11:52,059 --> 00:11:53,420
I won't forget that.

229
00:11:53,819 --> 00:11:54,899
So,

230
00:11:56,980 --> 00:11:58,259
I've got you.

231
00:11:58,380 --> 00:11:59,298
Do whatever

232
00:11:59,299 --> 00:12:01,099
you need to do.

233
00:12:02,980 --> 00:12:03,859
You make it all sound

234
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,940
so effortless.

235
00:12:07,140 --> 00:12:09,379
Doesn't it get exhausting,
carrying all of this alone?

236
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:14,019
Haven't you been carrying it

237
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:15,460
alone all this time too?

238
00:12:21,220 --> 00:12:22,300
Don't worry.

239
00:12:22,779 --> 00:12:24,538
We'll get through it,
one hurdle at a time.

240
00:12:24,539 --> 00:12:26,298
The Huo Group isn't that fragile.

241
00:12:26,299 --> 00:12:27,259
Neither am I.

242
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:28,180
So,

243
00:12:28,659 --> 00:12:30,058
go focus

244
00:12:30,059 --> 00:12:31,619
on your research.

245
00:12:31,939 --> 00:12:33,940
Leave the rest to me.

246
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,979
Have you thought about

247
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:39,139
who told you my identity?

248
00:12:41,579 --> 00:12:42,540
Not yet.

249
00:12:43,380 --> 00:12:45,818
But as you said,

250
00:12:45,819 --> 00:12:47,499
massive profits are involved.

251
00:12:47,579 --> 00:12:49,298
Whoever it is could
be getting desperate.

252
00:12:49,299 --> 00:12:50,859
So what's your plan?

253
00:12:52,299 --> 00:12:54,060
Find somewhere completely safe.

254
00:12:54,539 --> 00:12:56,499
Until this all comes to light,

255
00:12:56,579 --> 00:12:58,698
I'm going to hide you
somewhere no one can reach you.

256
00:12:58,699 --> 00:12:59,619
Okay.

257
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,540
I'll do whatever you say.

258
00:13:04,262 --> 00:13:09,507
♪Darling, you go far away♪

259
00:13:11,187 --> 00:13:15,532
♪Why don't you take me too?♪

260
00:13:17,962 --> 00:13:23,332
♪We could go on a journey♪

261
00:13:41,537 --> 00:13:45,311
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

262
00:13:45,312 --> 00:13:48,632
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

263
00:13:48,637 --> 00:13:52,011
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

264
00:13:52,012 --> 00:13:54,866
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

265
00:13:54,867 --> 00:13:58,707
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

266
00:13:58,787 --> 00:14:02,044
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

267
00:14:02,062 --> 00:14:05,748
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

268
00:14:05,749 --> 00:14:08,106
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

269
00:14:08,107 --> 00:14:12,346
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

270
00:14:12,347 --> 00:14:14,907
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

271
00:14:15,349 --> 00:14:21,747
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

272
00:14:22,549 --> 00:14:26,987
♪Let me hold you once again♪

273
00:14:27,237 --> 00:14:30,157
♪Resting against your chest♪

274
00:14:30,507 --> 00:14:35,748
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

275
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:40,548
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

276
00:14:40,549 --> 00:14:43,348
♪No reason needed♪

277
00:14:43,349 --> 00:14:45,546
♪My heart belongs to you♪

